---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Cohort">
  <h1>Cohort</h1>
  <p class="label">Our current research instrument</p>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Cohort is a lightweight web application we are building to test our central
      hypothesis: that shared social presence, meaning the awareness of others
      working on the same task at the same time, can improve focus among high
      school students without competition, leaderboards, points, or any other
      gamification mechanism.
    </p>
    <p>
      The tool is deliberately minimal. A student creates or joins a session with
      3 to 6 friends. Each participant can see who else is present and whether
      they are currently marked as focusing. There is no leaderboard. There are
      no streaks. There is no way to compare your focus time to anyone else's.
      The only information shared is who is here and whether they are working.
    </p>
    <p>
      This stripped-down design is a methodological choice, not a product
      decision. If we added points or competition, we could not know whether a
      focus improvement came from social presence or from gamification.
      Isolating the variable is the whole point.
    </p>

    <div class="panel">
      <p class="panel__label">Current status</p>
      <p class="panel__body">
        Cohort is in development. We plan to run structured testing sessions with
        volunteer students during the exam period in October and November 2026.
        We will report results in the devlog.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="links">
      <span class="muted">GitHub: coming soon</span>
      <span class="muted">Live version: not yet available</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
